definition:
(N.) fence.
(V.) mag-bakud, magpabakud ‘put up a fence’;
bakur-an ‘fence something in’.

(St./D.) prohibited. makabawal ‘prohibited’;
kabawalbawalan ‘really verboten’.
(V.) bawalan, bewalan ‘prohibit something’;
pa:mawal, pa:bawal, mamawal, pakibawal.

(N.) length.
(V.) kakabaq, kakaban ‘lengthen something’;
magpakabaq ‘stretch self’; pakikabaq;
ikabaq; a:kabaq; pakabaq; pakaban;
mipakabaq.
(D.) makabaq; makabakabaq.

(N.) marriage, wedding.
talakasal, kasal-wes ‘civil ceremony’.
(V.) kakasal, kinasal, ke:sal; ikasal;
magpakasal; pa:kasal; pa:ngasal; a:kasal;
mipakasal.
(D.) makasal, me:kasal.
